            <biogHist>
                <p>Donald Stewart, shepherd, was born in Perthshire but then moved to Park, Isle of
                    Lewis and became a factor. He was married to Isabella and they had at least six
                    children: Richmond, John, Helen, Mary, Grace and Jessie. Donald Stewart is known
                    for digging up the graveyards for land in and around Luskentyre, Sheilebost,
                    Nisebost and the Borves. </p>
